title: ASU's Tim White named Pac-12 Special Teams Player of the Week
text:
Special teams kept Arizona State in Saturday's loss at then-No. 4 Utah. Therefore, it's somewhat fitting that the Pac-12 on Monday honored one of the Sun Devils' special-teams players.
Junior Tim White is this week's Pac-12 Special Teams Player of the Week after returning a kickoff 100 yards for a touchdown in ASU's 34-18 loss in Salt Lake City. It marks the second time in three weeks an ASU player has been honored. Junior punter Matt Haack was honored two weeks ago.
Utah got the W, but Tim White gets the #12Best Moment of the Game for @FootballASU ! #ASUvsUTAH 
 https://t.co/a02Oz2nDmc
â€” Pac-12 Networks (@Pac12Networks) October 18, 2015 AZCENTRAL
ASU football rewind: Looking back at Sun Devils' loss at Utah
Against Utah, White -- a junior-college transfer -- returned four kicks for 169 yards. For the season, he ranks sixth nationally in kickoff returns, averaging 31.94 yards. His touchdown return was ASU's first since Rashad Ross opened the second half with a touchdown at Colorado in 2012.
As a receiver, White has 22 catches for 303 yards and five touchdowns. Overall, his six touchdowns tie sophomore running back Demario Richard for the team lead. For more on Tim White, check this out.
